Encyclopedia: A Stas-Rajko! One of the finest Zsiemsk-made motor carriages ever. An oldie but a goldie.
Stas-Rajko KK-2! One of the finest Zsiemsk-made motor carriages ever. An oldie but a goldie.

Encyclopedia: No. Only that the motor carriage is typically baby-blue, the colours of Zygismunt the Great, an ancient Zsiemsk ruler. His banners were famously zaffer and white: the colours of the Stas-Rajko.
You: "What happened last time, Kim?"
You: "Let me guess what happened last time, Kim: Blue and white are the colours of Zsiemsk. Someone painted it, got a Zsiemsk mad, and boom -- murder happened."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Could it be another Stas-Rajko murder?" He gives you a crooked smile. "Honestly, that just doesn't seem like the type of vehicle our dead guy would drive, so my initial guess is the two are not related."

Kim Kitsuragi: "People we're paid to protect." The lieutenant shakes his head. "Let's leave it at that."
Kim Kitsuragi: He studies his reflection in the car window. "Four years for murder in Reunion."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant shrugs. "The perps were remorseful. Their *sorry* knocked eight years off the sentence. That's the system."
Physical Instrument: Bulky frame. Heavy. Hardy. Looks like a tractor.
Encyclopedia: Zaffer blue was also the colour Zygismunt the Great used for his banners... Strange. This is really all you know about the Stas-Rajko. And ancient Zsiemsk rulers.
You: Who drives these?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, detective?"
You: "Hey Kim, check this out!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "A Stas-Rajko, KK-2. That's a classic model," the lieutenant replies with a nod. "Never thought I'd see another one repainted after what happened last time."
You: Hold on, maybe I can impress him -- do *I* know what happened last time?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Is that so, officer? I'll take you at your word."
Esprit de Corps: Were you there?
Jump to: [more_of_stas_rajko]
Kim Kitsuragi: "An old case from my precinct. A couple of Zsiemsk migrants saw a Stas-Rajko stopped in the street, painted just like this: muddy brown. Murdered the driver on the spot."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You sure you're not Zsiemsk?" He shares a smile with you, only for a second.
Encyclopedia: Yes, you're sure you're not! Or if you are, it's only in that Revacholian way. (Four to five percent maximum.)
Encyclopedia: Correction: four-thousand-three-hundred-and-ninety-five. The fourth largest public protest of a criminal trial in Revachol.
Kim Kitsuragi: "They said it was an honour killing. Hussar-style. The Zsiemsk community protested the trial, flying the colours." He shakes his head. "Five thousand came to protest."
Jump to: [more_of_stas_rajko]
You: What a beautiful motor carriage! I want to know more!
You: "Interesting. Before we proceed, I've got an *opinion* on this paint-job."
Encyclopedia: Not many people outside of Graad â€“ and Revachol West too, it appears.
You: Hold up. Is this a tractor?
Encyclopedia: Yes, built like a tractor. And used as one too in the Zsiemsk countryside! Take note of the Eight Antler emblem, the symbol of the Stas-Rajko. Proudly born to honour its humble roots.
Logic: The prisons in the Greater Revachol Industrial Harbour are already full. Prisoners are expensive to maintain. The longer the sentence, the larger the cost.

Encyclopedia: Glad to share! The value of the motor carriage has been seriously diminished by its colour: all Stas-Rajkos are baby-blue by default. The paint would be considered unforgivable to collectors.
Kim Kitsuragi: "That's... Well, yes. Exactly it, more or less. Except it was a crowd of them. Tore him out of the vehicle and ran him over with his own tyres."
